<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-08-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-08-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="125" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d125">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">611.9331/94½: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Coolidge</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Superior, Wisconsin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-08-11"><hi rend="italic">August
                                        11, 1928</hi>.</date><lb/>[Received August 11—9:50
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Letter 10th regarding Chinese treaty received. You may acknowledge that
                            signing of treaty is a recognition of the Nationalist Government.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Calvin Coolidge</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>